OL,3,CTougher rules proposed for benefit
OL,4,Ccheats in Guernsey
OL,6,FThe proposals outlined in the
OL,7,FCommittee's Policy Letter, 'Non-
OL,8,Fcontributory Benefit Rates for 2026',
OL,9,Frecommend that benefit-related fraud
OL,10,Foffences should be heard in either the
OL,11,FRoyal Court or the Magistrates Court.
OL,13,FIt also proposes amending penalties so
OL,14,Fthat the Magistrates Court is no
OL,15,Flonger restricted by specified limits.
OL,17,FThis change could allow the court to
OL,18,Fimpose a fine of up to #20,000 and/or
OL,19,Ftwo years imprisonment for a single
OL,20,Foffence, or up to three years for
OL,21,Fmultiple offences.
