OL,3,CTougher rules proposed for benefit
OL,4,Ccheats in Guernsey
OL,6,FAdditionally, it suggests increasing
OL,7,Fthe maximum penalty for all benefit-
OL,8,Frelated fraud offences to a seven-year
OL,9,Fprison sentence, bringing Guernsey in
OL,10,Fline with both the UK and Jersey.
OL,12,FDeputy Tina Bury, President of the
OL,13,FCommittee for Employment and Social
OL,14,FSecurity, says: "While the vast
OL,15,Fmajority of benefit claims are made
OL,16,Fhonestly and in good faith, deliberate
OL,17,Ffraud must be met with penalties that
OL,18,Freflect the seriousness of the offence.
